properties.Name: Language
properties.Description:
Language definitions are based on ISO 639.

ISO 639 contains much other information about the use of language symbols and registration of new symbols.

The language codes of ISO 639 are said to be "devised primarily for use in terminology, lexicography and linguistics, but they may be used for any application requiring the expression of languages in coded form."

Examples include:

ISO 639 CODES  LANGUAGE NAME  CODE     LANGUAGE FAMILY

ENGLISH         EN     GERMANIC
IRISH           GA     CELTIC
LATIN           LA     LATIN/GREEK
SWEDISH         SV     GERMANIC

LANGUAGE NAME  CODE     LANGUAGE FAMILY

ENGLISH         EN     GERMANIC
IRISH           GA     CELTIC
LATIN           LA     LATIN/GREEK
SWEDISH         SV     GERMANIC

Columns.Name: IsoLanguageId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an ISO Language.
